<plot>For the past five years, playwright and producer George Larkin corresponded with writers and artists in Baghdad and collected their stories about life during the war. In "Speaking of Baghdad," an acclaimed international cast performs the stories. We get a chance to hear from writers there about life during the war. We've heard from our media, government, pundits, and soldiers but little from the Iraqis themselves.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?509529</url></doc>
